- 2026-03-11 15:00 Successfully connected to local Opencode server and observed skill usage events
- 2026-03-12 09:00 Determined approach requires locally running Opencode server, which violates self-contained tool requirement

## Decision Log
- This will not work. I am abandoning this approach. The workflow requires a locally running instance of an Opencode server. This tool is meant to be exposed as a slash command. This means that everything needs to be self contained, managed programmatically. I, as the user, will not be booting up an Opencode server for the program to be a client of. I have therefore realised that my use of the Opencode agent needs to be managed as a sub process.

