## Notes & Blockers
- The Opencode Python SDK (v0.1.0a36) appears to be generated from an older OpenAPI spec than the current server (v1.2.24)
- Server rejects requests with Content-Type: application/json header when body is empty, causing 400 errors
- Workaround implemented: Custom httpx.Client that removes Content-Type header for empty-body requests
- Successfully demonstrated that skill usage can be detected via event streaming when connected to a local Opencode server
- However, the approach requires users to locally run an Opencode server, which conflicts with the requirement for tools to be self-contained and manageable programmatically
- Alternative approach: Manage Opencode agent as a subprocess rather than as a client to a separately managed server
- Key insight: The Python SDK expects the server to run on port 54321, but this is not well documented
